tml |archivedate=October 2, 2002 |url-status=dead |accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| rev2_PC = 4.5/5<ref name=Cincinnati/>\n| rev2_PS2 = 4.5/5<ref name=Cincinnati/>\n| rev2_XBOX = 4.5/5<ref name=Cincinnati/>\n| MC_GBA = 76/100<ref name=MCGBA>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/game-boy-advance/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for Game Boy Advance Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_NGC = 92/100<ref name=MCGC>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/gamecube/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for GameCube Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PC = 89/100<ref name=MCPC>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for PC Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PS = 85/100<ref name=MCPS>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for PlayStation Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_PS2 = 95/100<ref name=MCPS2>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-2/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for PlayStation 2 Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| MC_XBOX = 92/100<ref name=MCXB>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox/madden-nfl-2003 |title=Madden NFL 2003 for Xbox Reviews |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe GameCube, PlayStation 2 and Xbox versions received \"universal acclaim\", while the PC, PlayStation and Game Boy Advance versions received \"generally favorable reviews\", according to the [[Review aggregator|review aggregation]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name=MCGBA/><ref name=MCGC/><ref name=MCPC/><ref name=MCPS/><ref name=MCPS2/><ref name=MCXB/> In Japan, where the PS2 version was ported for release on December 19, 2002, ''[[Famitsu]]'' gave it a score of 33 out of 40.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=\u30d7\u30ec\u30a4\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f32 - \u30de\u30c3\u30c7\u30f3NFL \u30b9\u30fc\u30d1\u30fc\u30dc\u30a6\u30eb2003 |language=Japanese |magazine=[[Famitsu]] |publisher=[[Enterbrain]] |volume=915 |date=June 30, 2006 |page=85}}</ref>\n\n''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' gave it a perfect score twice, once from Ryan Boyce, who said that \"The folks at EA Sports... loaded this year's ultrarealistic game up with a slew of new features that include online play, a huge arcade-style training camp, and a nifty play creator that\u2019s so versatile that you can have receivers run pass routes that spell your name\";<ref name=Maxim>{{cite magazine |last=Boyce |first=Ryan |url=http://maximonline.com/entertainment/articles/article_4754.html |title=NFL Kickoff 2003 |magazine=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |publisher=[[Biglari Holdings]] |date=August 2002 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020804102900/http://maximonline.com/entertainment/articles/article_4754.html |archivedate=August 4, 2002 |url-status=dead |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref> and once from Scott Steinberg, who said that, \"Destined for the Hall of Fame, Madden's latest namesake (now in its 13th year) improves upon already stunning graphics and amps game play with faster speed and such fresh gridiron moves as sidearm passing and\u2014wahoo!\u2014gang tackling.\"<ref name=Maxim2>{{cite web |last=Steinberg |first=Scott |date=August 12, 2002 |url=http://www.maximonline.com/entertainment/reviews/review_games_3790.html |title=Madden NFL 2003 (GC, PC, PS2, Xbox) |website=Maxim |publisher=Biglari Holdings |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020905173933/http://www.maximonline.com/entertainment/reviews/review_games_3790.html |archivedate=September 5, 2002 |url-status=dead |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref> ''[[The Cincinnati Enquirer]]'' gave it four-and-a-half stars out of five, saying, \"Veteran players will be familiar with the feel of the game they grew up with, but there are certainly enough tweaks and new additions to justify its purchase.\"<ref name=Cincinnati/> ''[[BBC Sport]]'' gave the PS2 version 87%, saying, \"While 'NFL 2K3' still has slightly better graphics, Madden's updated controls, the excellent franchise features and its heavenly tactical play make it one of the best sports games ever to grace the PS2.\"<ref name=BBCSport/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n== Legacy ==\n''Madden NFL 2003'' was included in ''[[The EA Sports Collection]]'' in May 2004 along with other 2002 [[EA Sports]] games.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{moby game|id=/madden-nfl-2003}}\n*{{moby game|id=/gameboy-advance/madden-nfl-2003_|name=''Madden NFL 2003'' (Game Boy Advance)}}\n\n{{MaddenNFL-Games}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madden Nfl 2003}}\n[[Category:Madden NFL]]\n[[Category:2002 video games]]\n[[Category:Electronic Arts games]]\n[[Category:EA Sports games]]\n[[Category:Interactive Achievement Award winners]]\n[[Category:GameCube games]]\n[[Category:Game Boy Advance games]]\n[[Category:Game Boy Advance-only games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation (console) games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 2 games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Xbox games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2002 American football simulation video game}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Madden NFL 2003\n| image = Madden2003Box.jpg\n| image_size = 256px\n| caption = [[PlayStation 2]] cover art featuring [[Marshall Faulk]]\n| developer = [[EA Tiburon]]<br />[[Budcat Creations]]\n| publisher = [[EA Sports]]\n| series    = ''[[Madden NFL]]''\n| released  = {{vgrelease|NA|August 12, 2002|NA|August 13, 2002 <small>(PSX)</small>|PAL|September 27, 2002 <small>(PC, Xbox)</small>|PAL|October 4, 2002 <small>(PS2)</small>|PAL|October 11, 2002 <small>(GC)</small>}}\n| genre     = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes     = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n| platforms = [[Game Boy Advance]]<br>[[Nintendo GameCube|GameCube]]<br>[[Microsoft Windows]]<br>[[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]]<br>[[PlayStation 2]]<br>[[Xbox (console)|Xbox]]\n}}\n\n'''''Madden NFL 2003''''' is an [[American football]] [[simulation video game]] based on the [[National Football League|NFL]] that was developed by [[EA Tiburon]] and [[Budcat Creations]] and published by [[EA Sports]]. The 14th installment of the ''[[Madden NFL|Madden NFL series]]'', the game features former [[St. Louis Rams]] [[Running back (American football)|running back]] [[Marshall Faulk]] on the cover. This edition of ''Madden'' was the first to have [[EA Trax]], the Mini Camp mode and to feature [[John Madden]] and [[Al Michaels]] as commentators, who took over for [[Pat Summerall]]. Although it featured the expansion [[Houston Texans]] and the relocation of the [[Seattle Seahawks]] to the NFC, it was actually the second to do so (after [[Madden NFL 2002|the previous edition]] had it done in the second season of its own Franchise mode, with the Seahawks still in the AFC and no Texans team when said mode was started). The game was released on August 12, 2002 for the [[Game Boy Advance]], [[GameCube]], [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]], [[PlayStation 2]] and the [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]].\n\n==Roster errors==\n* [[Bruce Matthews (American football)|Bruce Matthews]] is the starting center for the [[Tennessee Titans]] despite having retired by the start of the season.\n* Retired [[quarterback]] [[Mark Rypien]] is listed as a free agent.\n* [[Ryan Leaf]] appears as a backup quarterback for the [[Seattle Seahawks]] despite retiring before the start of training camp.\n* [[LaVar Arrington]] does not appear in the game due to him not represented by the NFL players association at the time therefore preventing him from appearing in the game, however his name can be added.\n* [[Pat Tillman]] appears as a free agent despite retiring before the season to join the military.\n* [[Tony Boselli]] appears as a left tackle for the [[Houston Texans]], however he retired before the 2002 NFL season because of injuries.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n''Madden NFL 2003'' was the first [[EA Sports]] video game to feature [[EA Trax]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; width:50%; margin: 5px;\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#C8C8FF;\" | Madden NFL 2003 Soundtrack\n|-\n!style=\"background:#ddddee;\" | Artist\n!style=\"background:#ddddee;\" | Song\n|-\n|[[Andrew W.K.]]\n|\"[[Party Hard]]\"\n|-\n|[[Audiovent]]\n|\"[[The Energy]]\"\n|-\n|[[Dry Cell (band)|Dry Cell]]\n|\"Body Crumbles\"\n|-\n|[[Epidemic (band)|Epidemic]]\n|\"Walk Away\"\n|-\n|[[Good Charlotte]]\n|\"[[The Anthem (Good Charlotte song)|The Anthem]]\"\n|-\n|[[Hed PE]]\n|\"Suck It Up\"\n|-\n|[[Bon Jovi]]\n|\"[[Everyday (Bon Jovi song)|Everyday]]\"\n|-\n|[[Nappy Roots]]\n|\"[[Awnaw]]\" (Rock Remix ft. [[Marcos Curiel]] of [[P.O.D.]])\n|-\n|[[OK Go]]\n|\"[[Get Over It (OK Go song)|Get Over It]]\"\n|-\n|[[Quarashi]]\n|\"[[Mr. Jinx (song)|Mr. Jinx]]\"\n|-\n|[[Seether]]\n|\"[[Fine Again]]\"\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| GBA = true\n| NGC = true\n| PC = true\n| PS = true\n| PS2 = true\n| XBOX = true\n| na = true\n| Allgame_GBA = 3/5<ref>{{cite web |last=Marriott |first=Scott Alan |url=http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=38857&tab=review |title=Madden NFL 2003 (GBA) - Review |website=[[AllGame]] |publisher=[[All Media Network]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115192147/http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=38857&tab=review |archivedate=November 15, 2014 |url-status=dead |accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| Allgame_NGC = 4/5<ref>{{cite web |last=Hoogland |first=Mark |url=http://www.allgame.com/game.php?id=38854&tab=review |title=Madden NFL 2003 (GC) - Review |website=AllGame |publisher=All Media Network |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141115192153/http://www.allgame.com/game.